cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper analyzes the interaction between people's behavior in physical retail spaces and their Web behavior, serving as a proxy to their information needs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
